~ start
Samuel: O love, do not wanton with those eyes,\nThat fire which burns, and will not dim,\nThat flame which neither fades nor dies\nBut chars me, marrow, soul, and limb.
Samuel: My mouth has never once run dry\nWhen fixed upon that gaze of thine—\nNo desert heat, no summer sky\nCould parch me as those eyes divine.
Samuel: Your beauty is my greatest sin,\nThe altar where I've always knelt,\nThe hymn that rises from within,\nThe wound I've cherished as I've felt.
Samuel: White and blue, like winter shore,\nLike frost upon a chapel pane,\nI have returned to you before,\nAnd I shall turn to you again.
=> END